- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on individuals' subjective opinions on their interrelationships with interactive language features. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the relationship between language and social network features in measuring individuals' opinions on interrelationship. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a novel model to measure individuals' opinions on interrelationship. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also possible as the paper deals with social relationships and personality traits. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a model to measure the degree of opinions' asymmetry.
